// Aerio — project-wide build settings
//
// Forks: this is the ONE place to change the Apple Developer team
// and bundle-identifier prefix. Edit the values below and rebuild —
// no Xcode UI clicking, no pbxproj surgery required.
//
// Notes:
//   • DEVELOPMENT_TEAM resolves to the 10-character team ID Apple
//     issues to your Developer Program account. Find it via Apple
//     Developer → Membership → Team ID.
//   • BUNDLE_ID_PREFIX is the reverse-DNS prefix used by every
//     target's PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER. Each target appends its
//     own suffix (e.g. `.aerio`, `.aerio.TopShelf`) so changing
//     the prefix here automatically updates all of them.
//   • You will ALSO need to update the iCloud KVS store identifier
//     in SupportingFiles/Aerio.entitlements and Aerio_tvOS.entitlements
//     to match your bundle ID, plus the App Group identifier in
//     SupportingFiles/Info.plist for Top Shelf to work in your fork.
//     Those four strings live outside this xcconfig because Apple
//     entitlement files don't accept variable substitution.
//
// Wiring:
//   This file is the project-level baseConfigurationReference for
//   both Debug and Release configurations (see Aerio.xcodeproj's
//   PBXProject XCConfigurationList). Target-level builds inherit
//   these settings through the build-setting hierarchy unless they
//   explicitly override them — which they shouldn't, because
//   that's what this file is for.
//
// CocoaPods:
//   The target-level baseConfigurationReference slots are owned by
//   CocoaPods (Pods-Aerio_iOS.{debug,release}.xcconfig and the tvOS
//   counterparts), so we attach at project level instead. Pods
//   xcconfigs don't define DEVELOPMENT_TEAM or BUNDLE_ID_PREFIX, so
//   they don't shadow the values below.

DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = 47DTJ3Q67T
BUNDLE_ID_PREFIX = app.molinete
